Vercel Web Analytics Installation Complete
==========================================

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Next.js eHealth application.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` version ^1.6.1 using npm
- Package added to dependencies in package.json
- package-lock.json updated with new dependency tree

### 2. Root Layout Modification (src/app/layout.tsx)
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
- Integrated `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, placed after the closing `</QueryProvider>` tag and before the closing `</body>` tag
- Preserved all existing code structure and component hierarchy

## Implementation Details

The project uses the App Router architecture with TypeScript. The Analytics component was added to the root layout at `src/app/layout.tsx` to ensure it loads on all pages of the application.

The Analytics component is positioned:
- Inside the `<body>` element
- After all main application content (QueryProvider, AuthProvider, ThemeProvider, children, and Toaster)
- Before the closing `</body>` tag

This placement ensures that:
1. Analytics tracking is available across all pages
2. It doesn't interfere with the existing provider hierarchy
3. It loads after the main content for optimal performance

## Verification

✅ Build completed successfully (npm run build)
✅ No linting errors introduced in layout.tsx
✅ All existing functionality preserved
✅ Lock file properly updated

## Files Modified

1. **package.json** - Added @vercel/analytics to dependencies
2. **package-lock.json** - Updated with new dependency tree (489 packages added)
3. **src/app/layout.tsx** - Added Analytics import and component

## Notes

- The existing codebase had pre-existing linting warnings/errors unrelated to these changes
- The Analytics component was placed outside of React providers as recommended by Vercel documentation
- This implementation follows Next.js App Router best practices for integrating third-party analytics
